## Type Validation Rule

### Rule Name: types-validation

### Description:
Before implementing any new endpoint or modifying existing ones, ensure proper type validation by following these steps:

1. Check if the entity type exists in `/packages/types/src/entities/`
   - If yes, ensure it follows the naming convention `IEntityNameEntity`
   - If no, create the appropriate type definition first

2. Verify corresponding body request type in `/packages/types/src/@types/body-requests/`
   - Body request types should follow the naming pattern:
     - For POST: `IPostEntityNameBodyRequest`
     - For PUT: `IPutEntityNameBodyRequest`

3. Ensure payload consistency:
   - Body request types should extend or reference the main entity type when appropriate
   - Use `Omit<>` or `Pick<>` to derive from the main entity type
   - Example:
     ```typescript
     import { IEntityNameEntity } from "../entities/entity-name.entity";
     
     export interface IPostEntityNameBodyRequest {
         // Only include fields needed for creation
         field1: string;
         field2: number;
         // Omit auto-generated fields like id, createdAt, etc.
     }
     ```

4. Verify corresponding params to get query type in `/packages/types/src/params/`
   - Params types should follow the naming pattern using EntityName and METHOD:
     - For GET All: `IGetAllEntityNameParams`
     - For GET Specific: `IGetByIdEntityNameParams`

5. Ensure params consistency:
   - Example:
     ```typescript
     import { IEntityNameEntity } from "../entities/entity-name.entity.ts";
     
     export interface IGetAllEntitiNameParams {
         // Only include fields needed for creation
         order: "name-desc" | "name-asc";
         field2: IEntityName["propriety"];
         // Omit auto-generated fields like id, createdAt, etc.p
     }
     ```

6. Verify corresponding response to HTTP Requests is typed in `/packages/types/src/responses/`
   - Params types should follow the naming pattern using I + HTTPMETHOD + SERVICE METHOD + EntityName Response:
     - For GET All: `IGetAllEntitiesResponse`
     - For GET Specific: `IGetByIdEntityNameParams`

7. Ensure responses consistency:
   - Example:
     ```typescript
     import { IEntityNameEntity } from "../file";
     import { Paginate } from "../paginate";

      
     export type IGetAllEntitiesResponse = Paginate<IEntityNameEntity>;

     ```

8. Verify corresponding dto type to correct types type in `/apps/backend/src/modules/module-name/dtos/entity-name.dto.ts`
   - Every dto NEEED use `Exact` helper type to ensure :
     - For GET methods search type in: `/packages/types/src/params/`
     - For PUT or POST methods search type inside: `/packages/types/src/body-requests/`

9. Ensure implemented correctly:
   - Example GET method:
     ```typescript
     import {
        IGetAllEntitiNameParams,
     } from "@global-types/params/entity-name.params";
     import { Exact } from "@global-types/exact";
     export class GetMethodEntityParamsDto
        implements Exact<GetMethodEntityParamsDto, IGetAllEntitiNameParams> {
        @IsOptional()
        classify: IGetAllEntitiNameParams["classify"];

        @IsString()
        @IsOptional()
        search: IGetAllEntitiNameParams["search"]

        @IsEnum(modulesArray)
        module: IGetAllEntitiNameParams["module"]

        @IsNumber()
        @IsOptional()
        page: : IGetAllEntitiNameParams["page"]

        @IsNumber()
        @IsOptional()
        limit: IGetAllEntitiNameParams["limit"]
    }
     ```
   - Example POST method:
     ```typescript
     import { IPostCreateFileToEntities } from "@global-types/body-requests/entity-name.body-request";
     import { Exact } from "@global-types/utils/exact";
     export class IPostMethodEntityNameDto
        implements Exact<IPostCreateFileToEntitiesDto, IPostCreateFileToEntities> {
        @IsString()
        entityType: IPostCreateFileToEntities["entityType"];

        @IsNumber()
        fileId: IPostCreateFileToEntities["fileId"];

        @IsNumber()
        entityId: IPostCreateFileToEntities["entityId"];
     }
     ```

10. Controller Get Usage
   - All times when i use Get method need used @Query nestjs type to get DTO.
   - Example controller using GETDTO
   ```typescript
       export class IEntityNameController{
        @Get("/method")
        async getMethodName(
            @User() user: UserSession,
            @Query() params: GetFilesParamsDto,
        ){
          return await this.entityNameService.methodName({
            params,
            userId: user.id,
         });
       }
      }
   ```

11. Controller Post Usage
   - All times when i use Post method need used @Post nestjs type to get DTO.
   - Example controller using POSTDTO
   ```typescript
       export class IEntityNameController{
        @Post("/method")
        async getMethodName(
            @User() user: UserSession,
            @Body() payload: MethodEntityNameDto,
        ){
          return await this.entityNameService.methodName({
            payload,
            userId: user.id,
         });
       }
      }
   ```

12. Validation checklist:
   - All required fields are properly typed
   - No unnecessary fields are included in body requests
   - Proper use of optional fields with `?` notation
   - Consistent use of enums and custom types
   - Proper nesting of related types

This rule helps maintain consistency between entity definitions and API payloads, reducing runtime errors and improving type safety. 